comments.body:
@jwhonce What's the name for the "python tests with a local server" that you mentioned during scrum?  I want to make sure it's included in the new CI-job structure.

@edsantiago mind taking a peek at the names and comments here.  You spent a lot of time figuring how to make them pretty, I don't want to revert any of your efforts.

@baude This is the set of jobs and parallelism we talked about.  Please let me know what you think.

@edsantiago slightly different...I think your tool is plenty past the 80% "good enough" mark :smile:

I see there's a typo in the "Total Success" task, and I'd like to make at least one pass through all my comments...you know, fixing all the its -> it's :grin:

Then, I know @baude doesn't like bash, and I value your feedback, but man...the diff is HUGE.  Though I'd be perfectly happy with a even a cursory review, is there some way I can make it any easier to look at?

@baude @mheon PTAL, this is ready to be manually merged.

The "Optional release test" failure is expected.  I triggered it manually to confirm it correctly fails when finding `-dev` in the output of `podman info` ("2.2.0-dev").  This is most certainly the case, since this PR is not for a podman release :smile: Normally this task won't run, unless somebody presses the "trigger" button in the WebUI.

***note:*** After/before this PR merges, I/we need to update the repo. settings to make the 'smoke' and 'total success' tasks as required (under branch protection).  All in-flight PRs will need to rebase as well, so might be good to merge this during a "quiet" period.

/lgtm
/hold

@containers/podman-maintainers PTAL, I think it would be prudent to get this merged early in the week
